claim: Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor is claimed to be equal to all other fighters.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Currently , the only combat-ready fifth-generation fighters are the Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor , which entered service with the United States Air Force in 2005 ; the Lockheed Martin F-35B Lightning II , which entered service with the United States Marine Corps in 2015 ; the Lockheed Martin F-35A Lightning II , which entered service with the United States Air Force in 2016 ; and the Chengdu J-20 , which entered service with the People 's Liberation Army Air Force  (  PLAAF  )  in March 2017 .
